<i>have thwarted
treasure-hunting efforts</i>

18:14.702 --> 18:17.503
<i>for more than two hundred years.</i>

18:17.605 --> 18:19.972
Traditionally,
there was a flood tunnel

18:20.074 --> 18:21.941
that went from Smith's
Cove here,

18:22.043 --> 18:23.509
up to the Money Pit.

18:23.611 --> 18:25.911
So it cut right through here
somewhere.

18:26.013 --> 18:30.115
<i>In 1850, searchers
from the Truro Company,</i>

18:30.218 --> 18:33.185
<i>working at Smith's
Cove, unearthed evidence</i>

18:33.287 --> 18:36.155
<i>of five intricate box drains.</i>

18:36.257 --> 18:39.091
<i>They were constructed
