<i>Unfortunately, generations</i>

18:50.104 --> 18:55.007
<i>of repeated excavations have
destroyed important evidence.</i>

18:55.109 --> 18:57.042
<i>But if the Oak Island team</i>

18:57.144 --> 18:59.945
<i>can locate even one
of the box drains</i>

19:00.047 --> 19:02.748
<i>and trace it back
to the Money Pit,</i>

19:02.850 --> 19:04.483
<i>they may be able to shut off</i>

19:04.585 --> 19:06.785
<i>the booby-trapped
flooding system.</i>

19:06.888 --> 19:10.055
<i>They also may be able
to determine just</i>

19:10.157 --> 19:14.627
<i>who constructed the box drains
in the first place.</i>

19:14.729 --> 19:17.730
I think the Smith's Cove
work is gonna be instrumental

19:17.832 --> 19:20.833
in understanding what possibly
happened on Oak Island.

19:20.935 --> 19:22.201
You find the box drains...

19:22.303 --> 19:24.503
Box drains lead
to a flood tunnel.

19:24.605 --> 19:26.538
The flood tunnel leads to the
Money Pit.

19:26.641 --> 19:28.507
It all begins at Smith's Cove.

19:28.609 --> 19:32.578
When the finger drains came
together, they formed a "V",

19:32.680 --> 19:35.114
and that "V" would
be facing this way

19:35.216 --> 19:36.949
and came toward shore.

19:37.051 --> 19:40.152
So if we could find out where
the "V" is cut in through here,

19:40.254 --> 19:42.187
- that'd be significant.
- Okay.

19:42.290 --> 19:43.822
- You ready?
- Okay.

19:45.293 --> 19:47.927
This is quite the mystery.

19:48.029 --> 19:51.764
We want to see for ourselves
that this flood system is here

19:51.866 --> 19:54.700
and how much of it is real,
how much of it is just story

19:54.802 --> 19:57.636
that was expanded
over the years.

19:57.738 --> 20:01.840
<i>As the Ground Penetrating
Radar System is pulled back</i>

